  "interpretation": {
    "summary": "Simple global merge turns the crop-level duplicate problem into a usable full-pattern signal, but threshold-only suppression is not exact-graph safe yet.",
    "evidence": "Support thresholds raise precision but remove too many true boundary and corner vertices. Score thresholds can reach very high precision, but the high-precision settings lose recall. The best simple F1 setting still misses 107 of 1210 GT vertices and leaves 61 false positives.",
